a game
  must know its players
  must know whose turn it is
  must know the order of the players
  must announce the next player after a turn

  must know the size of the board
  must know which sides of the board belong to which player

  must know its pieces and where they connect
  must hand out a piece for each turn
  must keep track who placed which pieces where in which orientation
  must check that the piece that is placed is the one that was handed out for the turn

  must check that a piece is placed in a valid location
  must check if the game is over after a turn:
    1) there are no more open connectors
    2) the piece for the next turn has no valid place on the board
  must calculate the scores for each player after the game is over

  must disqualify players that make invalid moves
